<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>explorerlens</id>
    <version>35.5.0</version>
    <title>ExplorerLens — GPU Thumbnail Provider</title>
    <authors>ExplorerLens Project Contributors</authors>
    <owners>ExplorerLens Project</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens</projectUrl>
    <iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens/main/docs/assets/icon-128.png</iconUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens/blob/main/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens</projectSourceUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <tags>thumbnail explorer shell-extension gpu image raw comics pdf windows</tags>
    <summary>GPU-accelerated thumbnail provider for Windows Explorer (200+ file formats)</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
ExplorerLens is a Windows Shell Extension (IThumbnailProvider COM DLL) that generates
GPU-accelerated thumbnails for 200+ file formats.

**Supported formats include:**
- Images: JPEG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, HEIC, JPEG XL, GIF, BMP, TIFF, EXR, QOI
- Camera RAW: CR2, CR3, NEF, ARW, DNG, RAF, ORF
- Archives: ZIP, CBZ, RAR, CBR, 7z (cover image extraction)
- Documents: PDF, PSD, SVG
- 3D/CAD: glTF, STL, OBJ

**Key features:**
- DirectX 11 GPU-accelerated decode pipeline
- Sub-1ms L1 LRU cache + persistent L2 disk cache
- ETW structured telemetry
- LENSManager configuration GUI
    ]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/RajwanYair/ExplorerLens/releases/tag/v35.5.0</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
